cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use openfusion, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "openfusion: an open-source drop-in compound-model proxy"
abstract: >-
  openfusion is an OpenAI-compatible proxy that fans a prompt out to a panel of
  language models in parallel and has a judge model synthesize a single answer
  (mixture-of-agents). It is the open implementation of the idea behind
  OpenRouter Fusion, runnable on any OpenAI-compatible provider.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "openfusion contributors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/shahar-dagan/openfusion"
url: "https://github.com/shahar-dagan/openfusion"
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
keywords:
  - llm
  - mixture-of-agents
  - openai
  - proxy
  - fusion
